my intuition: the more compression applied, the more random/meaningless/devoid-of-correlation the output becomes. 

in theory, more compression might allow longer-range & more semantically-abstract dependencies to be captured, but that's hard to learn directly;

instead, BPE shines bc it compresses the semantically-irrelevant characters but leaves intact the smallest semantic units of subwords (prefixes, roots, suffixes) - and so contains maximum information to train on.

